Third-party components
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

wepi builds on, bundles, or fetches at runtime software from the following
upstream projects. Each remains under its own license; consult the linked
projects for the authoritative license text and copyright notices.

- pi / pi-agent-core (@earendil-works/pi-ai)
  https://github.com/earendil-works/pi
  The in-browser coding agent loop.

- container2wasm
  https://github.com/container2wasm/container2wasm
  Compiles the Alpine container image to WebAssembly and provides the runtime
  worker/mounter blobs that C2wSandbox loads. Licensed under Apache-2.0.

- Alpine Linux
  https://alpinelinux.org/
  The base image whose userland runs inside the container2wasm VM.

- wllama (@wllama/wllama), WebLLM (@mlc-ai/web-llm), LiteRT-LM (@litert-lm/core)
  Optional in-browser inference engines, loaded only when selected.

Runtime sandbox assets (out.wasm.gzip, imagemounter.wasm.gzip, worker.js, and
the Alpine rootfs) are not stored in this repository; they are fetched on demand
by `wepi-fetch-assets`. Their licenses are those of the upstream projects above.
